"```sql\nSELECT ps.duration\nFROM results r\nJOIN races ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId\nJOIN circuits c ON ra.circuitId = c.circuitId\nJOIN lapTimes lt ON r.raceId = lt.raceId AND r.driverId = lt.driverId\nJOIN pitStops ps ON r.raceId = ps.raceId AND r.driverId = ps.driverId\nWHERE c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'\nAND lt.time = (\n    SELECT MIN(lt2.time)\n    FROM lapTimes lt2\n    WHERE lt2.raceId = ra.raceId\n);\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the duration of the pit stop for the driver who set the fastest lap time (lap record) during the race held at the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit. It joins the necessary tables to find the race, the driver, and the lap time, and then filters to get the minimum lap time for that race."